name: Dell XPS 13 (late 2020)
good_stuff:
Nice 16:10 display
Compact chassis with premium build quality
Best-in-class performance and integrated graphics
Solid keyboard and touchpad
bad_stuff:
Limited port selection
Not-great webcam with no privacy shutter
Processor upgrades won’t be noticed by most owners
Runs unusually hot under load

name: Gigabyte Aero 15 OLED XB
good_stuff:
Color-accurate OLED screen
High-end gaming performance
Per-key RGB keyboard
Solid port selection
bad_stuff:
Nosecam
Display is dimmer than some creative laptops
The design isn’t for everyone

name: Acer Chromebook Spin 713
good_stuff:
Excellent 3:2 screen
Good keyboard
Great port selection with HDMI
Performance and battery on par with more expensive competitors
bad_stuff:
Bad speakers
No fingerprint sensor
Utilitarian design

name: Apple MacBook Pro 13 (two-ports, late 2020)
good_stuff:
Great performance
Excellent battery life
Great display
bad_stuff:
Only two USB ports
Can’t get more than 16GB of RAM
Miserable webcam
Touch Bar makes everything harder, not easier

name: Asus ROG Zephyrus G14
good_stuff:
Demanding games are playable
Sleek retro vibe
Comfortable touchpad and keyboard
Strong battery life for productivity
bad_stuff:
No webcam 
16:9 aspect ratio is cumbersome for productivity 
CPU gets hot

name: Apple MacBook Air (Late 2020)
good_stuff:
Fast
Intel-based apps work well
Excellent battery life
bad_stuff:
Awful webcam
iOS apps are a whiff
It’s time to admit Macs would be better with touchscreens

name: Dell G5 15 SE (2020)
good_stuff:
Incredibly capable for the price
It can run most games at 60 frames per second 
Great selection of components and ports
bad_stuff:
Clunky, all-plastic design
Light bleed on display
Occasional performance issues

name: Apple MacBook Pro (16-inch, 2019)
good_stuff:
Keyboard
Improved thermals
Best speakers on a laptop
Improved battery life
bad_stuff:
Heavy
No SD card slot
macOS Catalina is still buggy

name: HP Envy x360 (2020)
good_stuff:
Compact and sturdy build
Good keyboard
Strong gaming performance for integrated graphics
All-day battery life
bad_stuff:
No Thunderbolt 3 or HDMI
The 16:9 screen is the bane of my existence
There’s some bloatware

name: Lenovo Chromebook Duet
good_stuff:
Ultra portable
11-hour battery life
Included keyboard and kickstand
You can’t beat the price
bad_stuff:
Cramped keyboard and touchpad
Just one port (and it’s not a headphone jack)
Lacks the horsepower for serious multitasking

name: Dell XPS 15 (2020)
good_stuff:
Excellent 16:10 display
Upgraded bezel-free chassis design
Great keyboard and touchpad
Full-size SD card reader
bad_stuff:
Below-average battery life
Loud fans under load
Runs hot
Frustrating bloatware that affects performance

name: Dell XPS 13 2-in-1 (2020)
good_stuff:
16:10 display
Exceptional build quality
All-day battery life
Fast CPU with new integrated graphics
bad_stuff:
Shallow keyboard
No USB-A ports
Not-great webcam
CPU heat is pushing it

name: HP Elite Dragonfly (2020)
good_stuff:
Sure View Reflect screen
Tile tracker works
Exceptional keyboard
11-hour battery life
bad_stuff:
Expensive
Screen is quite glossy in privacy mode
Last-generation processors

name: Razer Blade Pro 17 (2020)
good_stuff:
Impressive gaming performance
Thin, chic design
Colorful keyboard with fun effects
bad_stuff:
Just a 512GB SSD in 300Hz models
Gets hot
Expensive

name: HP Spectre x360 13 (Late 2019)
good_stuff:
More compact design than prior x360 models
Finally, a good trackpad
Windows Hello-compatible camera and fingerprint sensor
Snappy performance, plus an integrated LTE option
bad_stuff:
Only average battery life
It’s time for the 16:9 screen to die
Annoying bloatware
